title: For Sale/Trade:  Heritage Colt 45
location: Washington (45 minutes north of), Evansville, Indiana
postcontent: A neat old piece of history...Heritage made this Colt a few years back and it's been carried/hauled in the woods, etc. from what I can tell.  The barrel is right at 7 1/2 inches and I've had it re-crowned where it was apparently dropped.  Nice case coloring.  A minor issue worth noting:If the barrel is tipped upward when the gun is cocked, the cylinder will not advance.  Upon investigation, we discovered that the flat spring attached behind the hand is gone do you have to tip the barrel slightly down so that gravity can do it's work and put the hand in position to advance the cylinder.  My gunsmith thinks that Hawes parts would fit this one as it reminds him of a Hawes.  It may be a simple fix, but since it shoots fine as-is and is not an expensive gun, I didn't bother trying beyond looking for Heritage parts and having no luck.  Otherwise, the gun functions fine and test-fired flawlessly and accurately.  The bore, for a gun that looks like it's been carried and has some cosmetic marks, is remarkably clean, which is why I included that picture. I found the gun to be very accurate in the test-fire.Price/Value is pretty firm.  Will consider trades, but will not travel.Indiana residents only (unless you are willing to receive shipment at an FFL near you and pay shipping), must show photo ID and complete bill of sale.  Can text REDACTED or message here.
